Test coverage — unit tests for all public service methods, including error paths
Test quality — assert on specific values/shapes, not just no throw
Edge-case tests — empty inputs, null/undefined, max-length strings, concurrent calls
Integration test isolation — each test owns its fixtures; no shared mutable state
Type safety — eliminate any casts; replace with typed interfaces throughout
Singleton lifecycle — provide explicit reset/teardown for singletons in tests
Dependency injection — all classes receive deps via constructor; no hidden getInstance() inside methods
Config layer consistency — single source of truth: env var → config file → runtime override, in that priority order
Config validation at startup — fail fast with a clear message when required vars are missing or malformed
Secret handling — secrets never logged, never serialised to JSON responses, always redacted before storage
Error taxonomy — typed error hierarchy with stable codes; no raw new Error(string) at call sites
Error propagation — errors bubble with context attached; no silent swallow (catch {})
API response shape — uniform { success, data, error, message } envelope on every endpoint
Input validation — all route bodies validated via schema (zod/joi/convict) before handler logic runs
Rate limiting — per-user/per-IP limits on all mutating endpoints, not just config routes
Auth middleware consistency — auth applied at router mount, not scattered per-route
RBAC granularity — roles map to specific actions, not just admin vs non-admin
Logging levels — structured logs with consistent fields (requestId, userId, duration); no bare console.log
Graceful shutdown — drain in-flight requests, close DB connections, deregister listeners before exit
Health endpoint depth — /health reports dependency status (DB, external APIs) not just process uptime
WebSocket reconnect — exponential backoff with jitter on client reconnect; surface connection state to UI
Pagination — all list endpoints accept limit/offset (or cursor); no unbounded queries
Caching strategy — cache invalidation is explicit and tested; stale reads are bounded by TTL
Bundle size — code-split by route; lazy-load heavy visualisation libs (Three.js, D3)
Accessibility — all interactive elements have ARIA labels; keyboard navigation tested in CI
i18n readiness — user-visible strings extracted to a single locale file; no hardcoded English in JSX
CI pipeline speed — unit tests run in < 60 s; slow integration tests gated behind a separate job
Dependency hygiene — no unused packages; pnpm audit runs in CI; lockfile committed
Documentation drift — README and docs auto-checked against actual routes/config keys in CI
Observability — distributed trace IDs propagated from HTTP request through WS events to LLM calls
